Salesforce Logging & Monitoring: Implementation & Test Plan

Overview

Connect Salesforce to Microsoft Defender for Cloud Apps (DfCA) to monitor security events across four threat categories: 

anomalous access

data theft

privilege escalation

security policy tampering

DfCA ingest Salesforce logs activity data primarily through Salesforce Event Monitoring APIs and other available activity sources.

MVP scope: Get the integration running, validate logs are flowing, configure alerts, then assess whether Salesforce Shield is needed for remaining gaps.



Setup

Prerequisites

Requirement

Salesforce System Administrator access

Microsoft 365 Security Admin or Global Admin rights

Defender for Cloud Apps licence active

Dedicated Salesforce service account (System Admin profile)

Step 1 - Connect Salesforce to Defender for Cloud Apps

How Defender for Cloud Apps protects your Salesforce environment

Go to https://security.microsoft.com

Navigate to Cloud Apps > Connected Apps > App Connectors

Click "+ Connect an App" → search for and select Salesforce

Click "Connect Salesforce" → authenticate using the dedicated service account

On the Salesforce OAuth consent screen, click Allow https://help.salesforce.com/s/articleView?id=xcloud.connected_app_overview.htm&type=5 

Initial log ingestion may take between 15 minutes and several hours depending on connector initialization and Salesforce API synchronization intervals.

Verify status shows "Connected" on the App Connectors page

Verify DfCA appears under Setup > Apps > Connected Apps > Manage Connected Apps in Salesforce



